<h3>Advocacy Groups and Technical Resources</h3>
<ul>

  <li><b>High Performance Wireless Research and Education Network (HPWREN): </b>A San Diego area research network funded by the National Science Foundation dedicated to "creating, demonstrating, and evalating a non-commercial, prototype, high-performance, wide-area, wireless network.<br>
<a href="http://hpwren.ucsd.edu/">http://hpwren.ucsd.edu/</a><br><br>
  <li><b>Wireless Networking Unit of the Aeronomy and Radio Propagation Laboratory (ARPL): </b>The host of the &quot;School on Wireless Networking for Scientific Applications in Developing Countries&quot; seminars. Their site archives presentations from past "school" events.<br />
  <a href="http://wireless.ictp.it/groups/wireless/">http://wireless.ictp.it/groups/wireless/</a><br />
  <br />
  </li>
  <li><strong>Wireless Africa: </strong>A group in South Africa researching ways to expand the use of wireless networking to developing countries<a href="http://wireless.ictp.it/groups/wireless/"></a>.<br />
  <a href="http://wirelessafrica.meraka.org.za/">http://wirelessafrica.meraka.org.za/<br />
  </a><br />
  </li>
  <li>
	      <!-- RIGHT COLUMN -->
            
		  <!-- Column 1 end -->
        <strong>Wireless Networking in the Developing World: </strong>An electronic book with information on how to build and maintain a wireless network in the developing world. <strong><br />
        </strong><a href="http://wndw.net/">http://wndw.net/ </a><br />
        <br />
</li>
<li><strong>Green WIFI: </strong>A volunteer organization dedicated to the spread of solar powered wireless networking equipment<strong>.<br />
  </strong><a href="http://www.greenwifi.org">http://www.greenwifi.org<br />
  <br />
  </a> </li>
<li><strong>WirelessU: </strong>A repository of technical documents about wireless networking and a community that promotes the spread of wireless networking.<strong><br />
    </strong><a href="http://wirelessu.org/">http://wirelessu.org/</a><br />
    <br />
</li>
<li><strong>MIT roofnet : </strong>A wireless mesh network operating in Cambridge, MASS. Contains technical documents on how to setup a wireless mesh network.<br />
    <a href="http://pdos.csail.mit.edu/roofnet/doku.php">http://pdos.csail.mit.edu/roofnet/doku.php </a><br />
    <br />
</li>
<li><strong>NSRC.org - Wireless Network Security Workshop: </strong>A collection of presentations about wireless networking and wireless network security. Topics ranging from an introduction to wireless networking to access point configuration and network traffic analysis.<br />
  <a href="http://nsrc.org/workshops/2008/ait-wireless/">http://nsrc.org/workshops/2008/ait-wireless/</a><br />
  <br />
</li>
<li><strong>SANS.org - A Survey of Wireless Mesh Networking Security Technology and Threats: </strong>An introduction to wireless mesh networks and a summary of the security implications that these networks present.<br />
  <a href="http://www.sans.org/reading_room/whitepapers/honors/1657.php">http://www.sans.org/reading_room/whitepapers/honors/1657.php</a><br />
  <br />
</li>
<li><strong>Open-mesh.org: </strong>A collection of information about Wireless mesh networking and the B.A.T.M.A.N. routing protocol.<a href="https://www.open-mesh.org/"><br />
  https://www.open-mesh.org<br />
  </a></li><br>
<li><strong>IEEE - Wireless: </strong>An organization that houses documents about  wireless standards such as 802.1. <br><a href="http://standards.ieee.org/wireless/">http://standards.ieee.org/wireless/</a></li>
</ul>

<h3>Wireless Projects</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Blantyre - Mangochi Wireless Backbone: </strong>A description of the project in Spanish (en Espa&ntilde;ol). <br />
      <a href="http://nsrc.org/db/lookup/report.php?id=72&fromISO=MW">http://nsrc.org/db/lookup/report.php?id=72&fromISO=MW</a><br />
    <br />
  </li>
  <li><strong>Blantyre - Mangochi Wireless Backbone Diagrams: </strong>Are available in PDF format.<br />
      <a href="http://nsrc.org/AFRICA/MW/Blantyre-Mangochi-backbone.pdf">http://nsrc.org/AFRICA/MW/Blantyre-Mangochi-backbone.pdf</a></br />
    <br />
  </li>
</ul>

<h3>Do-It-Yourself Projects</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>How To Setup A Home Network: </strong>Instructions for setting up your home nework with a modem and wireless router.<br />
      <a href="http://homenetworkadmin.com/how-to-setup-a-home-network">http://homenetworkadmin.com/how-to-setup-a-home-network</a><br /><br />
  </li>
  <li><strong>Cantenna: </strong>Instructions on how to create a WIFI antenna from a tin can.<br />
      <a href="http://www.turnpoint.net/wireless/cantennahowto.html">http://www.turnpoint.net/wireless/cantennahowto.html</a><br />
    <br />
  </li>
  <li><strong>Mini-satillite dish antenna: </strong>Instructions on how to create a WIFI antenna from a mini-satillite dish.<br />
    <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2005/11/15/how-to-build-a-wifi-biquad-dish-antenna/">http://www.engadget.com/2005/11/15/how-to-build-a-wifi-biquad-dish-antenna/</a><br />
    <br />
  </li>
  <li><strong>OpenWRT: </strong>A open source firmware used to add functionality to inexpensive wireless networking equipment.<br />
      <a href="http://openwrt.org/">http://openwrt.org/</a><br />
  </li><br>
 <li><strong>USB/Asian Parabolic Cookware Antenna: </strong>A website with instructions on how to make a WIFI antenna using a USB wifi
device and a Wok.<br>
<a href="http://www.usbwifi.orconhosting.net.nz/">http://www.usbwifi.orconhosting.net.nz/</a><br />
<br />
</li>
<li><strong>Seattle Wireless - Linksys WRT-54g:</strong> An in depth technical document about the Linksys WRT-54g.<br />
  <a href="http://www.seattlewireless.net/moin.cgi/LinksysWrt54g">http://www.seattlewireless.net/moin.cgi/LinksysWrt54g</a></li>
</ul>
<h3>Equipment Venders</h3>
<ul>

<li><strong>Alvarion: </strong>A manufacturer of WiMAX wireless products.<br>
<a href="http://www.alvarion.com">http://www.alvarion.com/</a></li><br>

<li><strong>Fleeman Anderson &amp; Bird: </strong>A vender of wireless networking equipment including connectors, antennas, access points, enclosures and mounts.<br />
    <a href="http://www.fab-corp.com/">http://www.fab-corp.com/</a><br />
    <br />
  </li>
  <li><strong>Inveneo:</strong> A company that manufactures low-power, low-cost computer and networking equipment designed for the needs of the developing world.<br />
  <a href="http://www.inveneo.com">http://www.inveneo.com<br />
  <br />
  </a></li>
  <li><strong>Meraki:</strong> A vender of wireless networking equipment specializing in wireless mesh networks.<br />
    <a href="http://meraki.com">http://meraki.com</a><br />
    <br />
  </li>
  <li><strong>Open-mesh.com:</strong> A vender of low-cost wireless mesh networking devices.<br />
      <a href="http://www.open-mesh.com/">http://www.open-mesh.com/</a><br />
    <br />
  </li>
  <li><strong>PCTEL, Inc</strong> A company that manufactures WIFI and WiMAX antennas.<br>
  <a href="http://www.maxrad.com/">http://www.maxrad.com/</a><br><br></li>

  <li><strong>Solectek</strong> A manufacturer of long-range broadband wireless products.<br>
<a href="http://www.solectek.com/">http://www.solectek.com/</a><br><br>
</li>
  <li><strong>Ubiquiti Networks: </strong>A vender of wireless networking equipment that is largely compatible with the OpenWRT framework.<strong><br />
    </strong><a href="http://www.ubnt.com/">http://www.ubnt.com/</a><br />
    <a href="http://meraki.com"><br />
    </a><br />
  </li>
</ul>
